Boast.ai is looking for a full-time Controller to build our financial and accounting operations from the ground up. If you like building and want to create the accounting function you have always wanted, this is the role for you. The ideal candidate gets excited by implementing financial systems and processes and working with the rest of the business to enable our teams to operate as effectively as possible. Reporting to the CFO, you will be the data and information foundation by which we make financial decisions. You will be responsible for the entire accounting function of Boast, as well as corporate & Board reporting. You will also onboard, develop, and grow your team as the company rapidly scales its business over the next two years. 
Responsibilities: 
As the lead member of our accounting team, you will be responsible for developing our accounting and finance capabilities overall. This includes development of our financial system of record, workflow procedures and management, and reporting capabilities. You will also serve as a key stakeholder in collaboration with our leadership and functional teams in developing reporting and insights that drive the business forward. 
Key responsibilities include: Primary responsibility for GAAP reporting; management of the general ledger and ownership of all journal entries Primary responsibility for core accounting functions including revenue recognition, cash management, payroll, accounts payable, and accounts receivable Prepare monthly, quarterly, and annual financial reports for our Board of Directors, creditors, and management team Hire, manage, and develop a high-growth accounting team with an expectation of excellence Develop, implement, and maintain Boastâ€™s financial systems, policies, procedures, and controls Oversee stock option and cap table administration Manage external vendors, including audit, tax and valuation efforts Comply with international, federal, state and local governmentsâ€™ legal and reporting requirements and filings Work with internal teams to develop internal guidance and support in order to drive successful growth and efficient scale 
Qualifications 
Experience in a position equivalent to a controller, with a proven track record of implementing accounting best practices. This often comes from: 6+ years of accounting experience, with 3+ years as a startup controller or assistant controller at a mid-sized company CPA certification or equivalentStrong technical accounting skills, particularly regarding technology companies Excellent written and verbal communication skills, and an ability work cross-functionally A self-started who anticipates problems and proactively finds solutions Experience with multinational corporations a plus Experience implementing financial systems (e.g., Netsuite or Intacct) a plus 
